I mentioned it will now be difficult ordering anything else.  For my main entree I ordered the pork chop, accompanied by sweet potato fries, broccoli raab, and applesauce. I really enjoyed my three-course meal during the Winter Restaurant Week. The light, textured crust of the mac and cheese was absolutely delicious. I ordered the Sobo Burger and it was delicious but big. I could only eat half. The finger potatoes were a different spin on having fries with a burger and they were also good. I wasn't feeling the salad though. It was a bit dry ... as in not enough dressing. It was like they flickered something that was in a weird grey area of tasteless yet sour. Nevertheless, I still enjoyed it. Finally, the apple pie came. Giving a sweet end to a wonderful meal.  I ate with a friend who ordered the seemingly popular Korean Chicken Fried Steak. He enjoyed the chicken fried steak, but found the improvised gochujang sauce overpowering. For his starter, he ordered the Grilled Stuffed Grape Leaves and it was pleasant for him. He said it was easy on the stomach for his main course. He, too, enjoyed the apple pie.

The only thing I wish is Google had a less than one star button because that would be a more accurate description of the experience.

I'm staying in Baltimore for the bar exam, and I decide to venture across the way, on one of the hottest says of the summer.  And I ordered the 3 spread platter with double hummus and one spicy feta.  It comes with sliced cucumbers and pickled carrots and some toast.  It was really good.  I also had a hot ham and cheese with the cherry mustard, which I was skeptical about, but I'm happy I took the leap.  The food was really good and the service was good too..

I recently started a new adventure with my paramour where we would have one day a month completely devoted to trying completely new places, doing completely new things and meeting new people. Our first stop on this journey happened to be Sobo Cafe!! I simply searched for "best brunches in Baltimore" and I came across Sobo's menu. The reviews were shining and I was excited to learn that Sobo is directly behind a market where I spent so much of my childhood. To start, our server was so extremely courteous and friendly he made us feel right at home! We arrivied during lunch and the Cafe had just opened for the day. My Fiancé and I started with Sobo's interpretation of a lunch time Mojito. It was very flavorful, but also light and not as heavily sweetened as others we've had. It was delicious!! The menu was full and diverse, but because it was our first time we both decided to try something simple. I ordered the Sobo turkey sandwich, and my fiancé ordered the Cesar salad with roasted chicken thigh meat added on. Both portions were fantastic! Her salad was very light, and had hints of lemon and black pepper, and the chicken was perfectly seasoned and cooked. My turkey sandwich was no less than the best turkey sandwich I've ever had. People may think that a turkey sandwich cannot differ in taste to most out there, but they would be wrong. The bread was homemade and delicious. The turkey came with crushed black pepper and some type of seasoning I couldn't even describe. I have never been a fan of tomatoes, yet the sandwich came with roasted cherry sized tomatoes that were so tasteful I found myself eating them whole. With the organic food, the amazingly friendly atmosphere and the superb service we experienced,  I cannot express how happy I am with Sobo and we will most certainly be back for more!!!

I've gone for brunch and dinner and the food is always very good and very reasonable.  It may take a little while to come out if it's busy, but it's worth it.  One of the few quality restaurants to go out for a nice dinner in Federal Hill.

This is most definitely a place for an awesome dinner (which I missed unfortunately). The lunch menu is great too, though limited to primarily sandwiches. The French Dip sandwich goes down well with Resurrection ale (7% abv). The staff is very friendly. The neighbourhood is cool. Don't see what's not to like about it.
Amazing restaurant with a good local beer/wine selection

I'm not even done with my food yet and had to rate this restaurant 5++ every item we ordered, Mac and cheese, burger, and smoked salmon sandwich...are all phenomenal. New favorite ♡ we're coming back to try everything on the menu.
Fantastic independent restaurant in the heart of Federal Hill.  The owner is almost always around and takes time to personally greet all her patrons.  Nice happy hour specials and a delicious menu.
SOOOOOO GOOD!! Exceptional Mac and Cheese!!!!

(Translated by Google) Small place, better to book in advance, fast and attentive service. In our table of eight people the dishes were all well presented, but above all, good !!! Definitely recommendable place !!!!  (Original) Locale piccolo, meglio prenotare con anticipo, servizio rapido e attento. Nel nostro tavolo formato da otto persone i piatti sono stati tutti ben presentati, ma soprattutto, buoni!!! Locale da consigliare sicuramente!!!!
Amazing smoked salmon omelette- very warm and attentive service - relaxed ambiance... They had their stuff together!  Good location away from the crowded part of cross street ... I'll be back soon :)

They have delicious fresh baked bread. If you ever have a chance to try the apple bread, do it! They have great vegetarian options - no boring pasta and veggie burgers here. My favorite is the shakshuka.
Delicious food. Went for breakfast 2 times. Will be back!

OK lets get the facts straight! If you go to this restaurant you will be back within the a 2 week period i came back the same week. This is not an alright restaurant. Thet have a PASTRY CHEF! and the HEAD CHEF is NO JOKE. 7 things on there menu can easily be your favorite dish at a restaurant. Ok im done
Food and service were excellent. Very accommodating to infant and stroller although no changing table in bathrooms.
New owners spruced it up. Fed hill staple. Go now

The friendly owners always make you feel very welcome. The portions are excellent, as well as a great selection of wine and beer. Heavy Seas on tap pairs excellent with the rich and "homestyle" dishes. A cast of odd regulars shuffle in and out all evening, making sobo cafe a great place for conversation,food, and heady beverages.
Great meal, cool art work.  Try the meat muffins.
